name: Trina Gray
bio: I help women get paid for their love of fitness so they can live an upgraded life with choices and purpose. Fitness mentor, wife, mom of college kids.

social_posts.post_text: Nothing about construction moves quickly. So we’re just enjoying watching the seasons change from summer to fall to winter over our new two-story addition. A guest suite, home theatre, office & workout room. Not huge, but helpful! With delays in lumber, hunting season, and the crew juggling other projects, this is where we are. Hoping for a roof soon. When will it be done? When it’s done. Lol.

Marriage Equality passed today. 

No one explained her thoughts better than @glennondoyle 

i wasn’t holding my breath and i’m not rejoicing, because i already knew…

so it’s not my big day. 
nothing was decided about me, here in this room. today all that was revealed was the character of some lawmakers in that room.

i wasn’t holding my breath. I breathe deep and free and easy with her. 

we knew. we know.
you do, too.

A lesson about protecting your peace. I envision that we all live in our own snow globe. Inside are your most important people — you, your closest loved ones, (spouse, kids, friends, chosen family & pets). 

Keep the chaos & noise of the world outside your snow globe. 

Keep the tranquility inside.

Rest in peace, beautiful mama. 

You lived your life in full color. After raising four kids, you danced into your next chapter of life. From riding horses in the mountains, to training your golden retrievers to be therapy dogs and competing in agility trials, to taking fitness classes, enjoying life with dad and following the adventures of your grandkids. 

You always showed up with a smile. One of my best friends said that she stood taller in your presence. Another said you were always graceful and elegant. I would say that you encouraged people around you to level up and see the day from a sunnier place. 

You and dad showed the world 55 years of marriage looks like. You loved each other until the end and you will in the next life.

You fought breast cancer and you won, over and over again, far outliving the doctors predictions. You were beautiful, strong and active, never fitting the mold for age. You soaked up every ounce of 81 years.

Enjoy your reunion with your beloved dogs. I hope you have blue skies and open fields to run in. I will always love you. ❤️

Merry Christmas. 

It was a weekend filled with low key, fun celebrations — at my in-laws, Jeff’s house & my home. Great food, thoughtful gifts. But it’s the people for me. 

A few pictures from today. It’s beautiful in our neck of the woods.

Grief is a strange beast. IYKYK. 
It comes in waves of sadness, wondering, feelings of gratitude, numbness, sometimes ignoring, sometimes accepting. 

My mom passed away last week, at 81 years old, on the Winter Solstice. I've been pouring over pictures, videos, and photo albums. Just remembering what it felt like to live those memories.

Grieve how you want. 
You can hide from the world, or keep showing up. 
You can cry a lot, or not at all. 
You can remember all of it, or just the good. 
You can hold on, or you can let go. 

I'm a writer. It's therapeutic. It's helpful. It's for me. It's for you. I share this to offer ideas or reassurance if you need it. 

PS - this picture is from Christmas a few years back, we took my parents to Turks & Caicos for a quieter beach holiday! My mom loves horses, so this was a treat.

Open up the champagne. 
Pop. 🎵🍾

Celebrating the New Year, and looking back on 2022. 

Feeling grateful for our kids, their journeys, our home, careers we love, fitness, friendship, travel, and peace of mind.
Six months of being your wife passed in the blink of an eye. Thanks for standing by me through it all.  Let’s go honeymoon. ☀️🥂

A bombshell of a call. 
On a much needed getaway. Beachbody (now BODi) called. 
Congratulated me & my team. 
Achieved 11 x Elite. 
A top online fitness team. 
11 years straight.
It really happened. 
It’s rare air. 
Only a few have been here.

The title is fun. 
But the work behind it is better. The workouts. The friendships.
The hours reading, thinking.
Podcasts, books, growth. 
Walks by myself. Inspiration. 
Rallying others.
Building a team of coaches. 

Sharing my experience. 
Speaking on zooms.
Presenting on stages. 
A lot of showing up by myself.
When no one asks or notices. 
Getting ideas, teaching others.
Moving through the ups & downs.
Getting better as a leader. 
As a woman. 
That’s the journey. 

11 x Elite. 
My stomach flips when I write it.

The thanks are endless. 
But IYKYK that you matter. 
Coaches, friends, peers. 
My family in Alpena. 
Lets celebrate.
Fitness fires me up. 
Changing lives fills me up. 
Let’s get after it.

Sometimes you have to disconnect to reconnect. 

The past month has been full of emotion. A mixture of grief, sadness & peace. Along with success, happiness and good in other areas of life.  That is the rollercoaster of life.

Our planned getaway to a concert in Riviera Maya came at the perfect time to regroup.

PS - my favorite picture from the trip is the first one, my wife in her element. Live music, warm breeze & time together.

Then and Now. 2006 ---> 2023 
I opened Bay Athletic Club on Monday, January 16th, 2006. 

My son Colt was only 5 months old (such a happy baby!) Now he's 17 years old, a high school senior who lifts and works at BAC as a busy student athlete. He's literally grown up there. 

Since the moment he was born, he came along for the ride, in his baby Bjorn carrier, during all my business planning, bank meetings, construction meetings, staff interviews, etc. We were holding on for the wild ride. 

I had a vision for creating an affordable hub of for people of all ages and stages of life to live happy and healthy. From students, to working parents, to retirees. I wanted to reach people who felt lonely, or hopeless, as well as those who already loved fitness. We could all belong. I saw it in my head before it ever came to life. With the help of many, it did. 

It has grown beyond my dreams. I lit a spark and hundreds of others have carried the torch. So many incredible teammates have given their time, talent and energy over the years. I'm grateful for the time people spend with us. 

So many members have lost weight, gotten stronger, met friends, reduced medications, overcome health issues, and changed their lives from the inside out at BAC! 

Over 17 years, we've served thousands of members, logged more than 1.5 million check ins, taught 25,000 group fitness classes, donated than more $50,000 to local causes, and been open 362 days per year! 😳

Let the journey continue! Alpena needs us, we need you!

Starting the year with a BANG! (Scroll through pics to see why!) I've been a BODi (formerly Beachbody) coach for 14 years), 11 times in a row as a top team. 

I partner with BODi to do two things: 
1. Help people get healthy from anywhere using at-home workouts, simple nutrition and accountability. Love it. 

2. Mentor women to set up their own home-based fitness businesses. Love it even more. 

Success is WAY more fun when you pass it on. Here are just a few of the fun accomplishments on my team this month. 

They are positive, fun women from CA to OR to WI to MI to NJ. Some are fitness instructors, some are stay at home moms, others are studio owners or entrepreneurs, former athletes, former competitive cheerleaders and some who lost their way and fitness brought them back. All are creating a life on their terms, with help from their at-home business. 

Link in bio if you ready for 2023 to be a year of growth, new opportunity, and friendships.

I woke up feeling heavy today. In my mind & heart. The weight of grief, worry, wondering. 
The anger of feeling misunderstood & years of shouting in the wind.
They never heard me.
But I knew me. 
And I find peace in that.

Yoga helped. 
This poem helped. 

if the pain was deep
you will have to let it go
many times 
@yung_pueblo

We need peace in two places: our head & our household. ✌🏼

Every place else is a jungle & we’re just trying to navigate. 😳

This is one way I release stress, find ideas, and create calm. Moving. Lifting. Stretching. 🧘🏻‍♀️

If you’re local, meet me at BAC. It’s my happy place outside of home. 💪🏼

If you’re not local, let me help you create a healthy habit at home. This one small part of my day affects everything else. DM. 🤍

In addition to being a club owner and mom, I'm a business mentor. I love it. 
I help women across the country to have an income from home in fitness. 

We used to be called coaches, which I'm proud of. Now we've become partners in the company, BODi. Change feels good. 

Having extra income reduces household friction, and offers choices to families. When I set up my own online business, I wanted to pay off an old Blazer and get a vehicle with working AC. I wanted to save up for a family trip to Maui. I wanted to have extra spending money for kids' activities, a paddle board, and plane tickets. I did all those things and more. I remember renting a huge inflatable bounce house for our yard for the kids' combined party. I was really proud. I could get paid to help people anywhere be fit. 

Whether you want to pay off debt, set up savings, have supplemental income or a rainy day fund, this is an option for you. 

If you enjoy healthy living and are willing to help others, spend $15 month to be a partner in your own business, it's less than the cost of lunch. 

Link in bio. Let's partner up :) I'l show you the way. Simple business plan, solid support, from a top team in the entire company 11 years straight! 

Disclaimer: BODi does not guarantee any level of success or income with the Coaching business. Each coaches income is dependent on his/her own effort, skill and diligence. Please see our statement of Independent Coach Earnings for the most recent info on actual incomes of our Coaches.

This blew me away. 😭

This morning I opened a huge, white box that arrived in the mail. 

It was a custom-made, beautiful backpack from leaders on my coaching team. We achieved a top, Elite team in the country again… 11 years in a row. 

There are only a few other people in the country who’ve done this. And I couldn’t be more proud. 

Because it represents a team. It represents leadership. It represents changing lives. It represents the ups and downs of life and showing up anyway.

I did it with the love and support of the women on Team Rockstar Fit. 

Friends who believed me when I didn’t, teammates who cheered me on, and who built businesses in health and fitness alongside me. 

Thank you to my team. TRSF, you are one of the biggest gifts in my life and one of my greatest joys. 

I will wear this with pride. TRSF proud. 

PS - if you need a hype squad of positive women to do life with, this might be your year. Reach out to me in a DM or fill out the coaching application in my bio. Let’s see if we are a good fit. Must have a positive attitude, be goal-oriented, and committed to health & fitness. I love mentoring and paying it forward.

I show up every day because I like the work as a coach & business partner in BODi (formerly Beachbody). 

Getting fun gifts in the mail for a job well done is fun too. Even as adults it’s fun to earn prizes. Love this Elite jacket & thermos. 

Thank you @bodi for making us feel seen!

Dreams take roots and lots of different ways. 

20 years ago, I read two books: “No B.S. Wealth Attraction for Entrepreneurs” and “No B.S. Business Success.”

I had none of those things. I was new to a small town and didn’t have a business, much less a job. 

But I devoured those books. I’d walk on the beach and think about them. I made a decision to create the life that was in my head. I didn’t know how, I didn’t know when, but I got to work, with support from key people in my life. 

I shut off the noise of others. I created businesses. Several of them. Local & online. I found joy in them. I built them. 

I grew a life worth dreaming about. Not by talking, by doing.

I was born & raised in the Midwest & have always loved all four seasons. 

Yes, it’s cold right now and my southern friends think that below zero life is crazy. Lol. 

But the winter sky over the lake is so pretty. I love our corner of the world.

No matter what it looks like right now, there are always blue skies ahead. 

(And even balmy 50 degree temps in February. Crazy!)

A friend reached out to me today. She noticed that I always “show up” for others in life, when it’s easy, or when it’s harder. It meant a lot. 

Maybe you’ve struggled with a loss, or a family issue, or a relationship or a failure, or a disappointment. Keep showing up. 

The emotions fade, new thoughts form & the skies always clear up.

On top of the world. 🗻
☀️Serving on the Coach Advisory Board for BODi (formerly Beachbody).
☀️Attending a mountain retreat alongside, bright, humble leaders.
☀️Doing what I love — business & fitness with people I admire.
☀️Being a mom who loves my work too, living out my purpose.

I have found that solitude, sunshine, and workouts by myself, are daily doses of therapy. 

I feel like I was born to be a journalist, and I found my way into fitness. I love that too, but I also love to write. 

I’ve been quieter on social media, trying to find my voice at times. We all have a story, we all have a journey and it’s ours to tell. 

I love the adventures of life and I have moved through struggle like everyone else has, and I believe that I always find joy and strength. 

Around the time that my mom passed, a family member who I’ve been distant from for years told me that I live my life like a “pitiful victim” on social media. I’ve never felt that way. On the contrary, I like to think that showing the struggles, showing the imperfections, showing the mistakes and showing the path to love and forgiveness and success in different areas of life is one that could help others. 

That attack has silenced me for a while. Today I decided to start writing again. Not always, maybe not even often. But enough to remember my voice. 

You have the right to live your life. Be kind and humble on the way. But don’t be intimidated by other people or their empty words. 

I feel like I was put on this planet to write, to help others, to lead, to raise my kids, to love, to live in full color. I wouldn’t trade it for anything.

location.city_name: Rainbow Falls, Great Smoky Mountains National Park

social_posts.post_text:
More wandering.
Less worrying.
More nature. 
Less tech. 
More days like this. 
Smoky Mountain National Park
Not your typical Monday. ⛰️🖤

Note to self: start more days with coffee in a hot tub overlooking the mountains. 😉

It’s fun to show highlights of this trip, but I don’t pretend that it happens easily. There is unsung work behind the scenes of owning a business to make trips like this happen. Late nights, early mornings, reading, leading, and learning.

If you’ve ever wanted to own a small business & you like fitness, let me help. 

I love my health club, but I wouldn’t recommend taking on the debt & responsibility of a huge bricks and mortar business. But owning something online is manageable and affordable.  And creates more options in life! Link in bio for info on my coaching team.

On international women’s day, it’s fun to celebrate female friendship, laughter, and love. 

It’s fun to celebrate our daughters wives, mothers, mentors, and other important women in our lives. 

On international women’s day, it’s also important to acknowledge that we have miles to go before we sleep. 

We have a glaring pay gap, where full-time working women make $.83 on the dollar to full-time working men in the US. 

We are grieving the loss of reproductive  justice, access to basic healthcare and control over our own bodies. 

We need more women in positions of leadership, elected office, higher education, and in all rooms that decisions are made. 💕

Inside our BAC team meeting today, still going strong after 17 years. Lots of laughter & even some tears. We shared success stories, competed in trivia, won prizes, created posters, took pictures, participated in team building, and more. The team is the heart beat of a small business. BAC proud. ❤️💪🏼
Collect memories, not things. ☀️⚓️🥽🐢🐠🧡
I couldn’t ask for a better trip, and I couldn’t ask for a better son to spend it with. I didn’t capture many pictures, but I’ll never forget it. 🐢🐠🤿💪🏼🌴☀️

My friend, Danny and I cohosted a reception in Riviera Maya. We invited women on our BODi (formerly Beachbody) team to join us with their family members at an ocean kiosk.

We are all women who partner with BODi to stay healthy ourselves, and to get paid to help others. 

There are teachers and financial planners and realtors and nurse practitioners and trainers and stay at home moms. We are all a part of a larger organization that I founded 14 years ago called Team Rockstar Fit.

We are on a paid vacation in Mexico as a reward for helping others in our lives get healthy in the past year, with workouts, every morning! I couldn’t dream up a better work trip. 

Nothing about this is built overnight. It’s built over many nights. I’ve been building my at home business for 14 years. If other people come and go, if other people critique, or if other people support, it doesn’t change my views. I love having a business that I can do from anywhere. 

If you’ve been watching me over the past year or years, please send me a DM, or even better fill out the application in my bio. 

I do a lot of coaching one on one. I’ll hop on a zoom with you and talk to you about your goals and dreams and your beliefs. If I can help you get started, I will. 

Team Rockstar Fit is an 11 time top team in this company. The team you join matters. We are welcoming and supportive. If we are a good fit, we will know it!

Lacee & I are both group fitness instructors & trainers. We both won national awards from IDEA Health & Fitness. 

She’s a new high energy Super Trainer for BODi (formerly Beachbody) and I’ve been a top coach in the company for more than a decade.

To all my fit pro friends, you can do both. Lead your own in-person fitness (classes, camps, boot camps or PT sessions) AND partner with BODi to offer online fitness. It just makes sense. 

Grow your business, expand your reach, partner with a top brand & be part of a fitness mastermind. 

@ideafit @thecurvygirltrainer @bodi

I’m wired as an enneagram 3. IFYKYK. I like achievement, leadership & am pretty dang independent (and impatient 😉). 

Earning this rewards trip from BODi (formerly Beachbody) fills my cup. 

But having 60 other women across my team earn it & take their spouses & families to Riviera Maya makes my cup run over. 

I love mentoring women to have their own online fitness business. I especially click with helpers & achievers. If that’s in your DNA, message me or fill out coach application in bio today. 

I’ll show you how to partner with BODi to earn income, make fitness-minded friends & even travel! Let’s start in April. I’m coming off a month of travel & am ready to pour into you.

She earned the hat.
She deserved the crown. 

So before you attack Angel Reese's looks, her character and everything else, consider this. You might not like that LSU won. (I was cheering for Iowa). You might not like her gloating or taunting in the wildest moment of her life. And you can be right. 

But when women resort to calling her trashy, trampy, swampy, ghetto and slutty, you just gave away ALL our power. 

When we don't like how a woman acts, or shows her emotion, in her own way, we resort to name calling, sexualizing and attacks on her appearance. 

She dominated on the court again today (34 double doubles, an NCAA record), people betting against her at every turn.

So when she reaches the top? It's hers to own. I bet that has been brewing inside her. And you don't have to like her. But the hate you give...

Thrive where you are planted. 

I grew up outside a capital city & later lived in fun college town. It was colorful & adventurous. 

Life changed & I moved to a small town 20 years ago. I love it and have built a life & family here. But sometimes I wonder.

Tonight I came home to this beautiful sunset & felt so peaceful. I trust that I’m where I’m meant to be.

What a difference a day makes.

There are 24 hours between these pictures in our backyard… from a mountain of ice blocks to open water & a warm burst of orange. 

I have gotten more comfortable experiencing change in life. Without pushing against it or always trying to fix it. And even trusting it. Sometimes it feels drastic or sudden. Whether it’s a friendship you need to move on from, a job, family situation, or any change in life. What feels drastic, becomes a new normal, and the days go on.

As an entrepreneur of 17 years, I can work from anywhere. But I prefer a space that’s peaceful and uncluttered. 

My first home office had a dial-up modem, a desk from college and a view of the wall. We moved, and I set up shop in my “cloffice” or closet office.” It was an old home and I think it was meant to be a sewing room. I had a view of a telephone pole and bulletin boards dotted my walls. 

We moved again, and I upgraded to a spacious bright office with a beautiful view. It felt like I had won the lottery. 

Years later, I moved again. My home office was carved out of my bedroom, like a little cubicle. That’s where I’ve been for the past four years. I’ve loved my view of the lake & a lot of sunshine, but the work was always present. 

Today I moved into my new home office, we’ve been working on a home addition since last fall. I’m just getting things set up, and it feels good to have designed it myself top to bottom. It fits me. 

It sure is fun to look back on the journey. The books, notebooks, awards & benchmarks have added up to career in fitness that I have loved.  Let’s see what I can make happen in this space.  I’m open to the journey.

I started working out in 1997 and never looked back. At the time, I was a senior in college and found myself out of shape, overweight, and feeling lethargic. I had lost the athlete I had been in high school. I didn’t know how to stay active, until I joined a health club. That investment in myself changed my life. 

Over the years I have taught thousands of group fitness classes at BAC & done with my own workouts at home with BODi. 

Today I worked out for the first time in my new home gym (a goal I set a year ago!) My 21-year-old self is proud that I’ve stuck with it this long — through marriage and parenting and business and grief and joy and the craziness of life. 

Fitness is a way of life. It’s who you are. Be her now! 💪🏼☝🏼❤️

May 2002 ===>> May 2023 
I have always been active, but a year ago, I needed a plan. I lost 10 lbs & 11 inches. I've kept off. I feel stronger. I don't diet. I don't live rigid. I help others find a plan. 

If you need support, and are ready to invest in your health, I run monthly text threads for women across the country. We follow a lifting program from BODi, have a healthy shake, lots of water, and a daily text. Simple. You can live anywhere. Next group starts after Memorial Day. Link in bio and comments. 

PS - If local, you are always invited to BAC to lift or workout. It's the best.

"Your life is short and rare and amazing and miraculous, and you want to do really interesting things while you're here. And the clock is ticking, and the world is spinning, and we simply do have time anymore to think so small." - Elizabeth Gilbert, Big Magic 

I was recently asked to speak on stage in San Antonio at the BODi Annual Summit this summer. (Are you going!) BTW, BODi is formerly Beachbody, but we ditched the baggage that came with the name. 

I have butterflies already and I never take this opportunity for granted. BODi has changed my life and I pay my ideas and belief forward. 

I've been honored to speak on their stages for a decade (a few photos attached). I continue to show up to inspire other women to keep betting on themselves, keep redefining themselves, and stop playing small. No one benefits when we do. 

PS - My kids Jade and Colt have watched this journey and been a part of it since they were toddlers. They have seen the successes and the struggles of being a leader. I know without a doubt as they enter the world as their own amazing humans, they will be equipped to handle the hard and inspired to share their light, too.

I’ll take a tall order of sunshine & time with my kids. 💛

Prom & Mother’s Day 2023
Now & Then. 👨🏻‍🎓

I help women turn their own fitness journey into income so they can do more things they love -- from floating on a flamingo, to visiting kids at college, to paying for kids sports, to spa days, to concerts, to donating locally, to renovation projects, to adding to retirement or paying off debt. 

All things I love. :)

PS - As a coach with BODi for 15 years, I've helped hundreds of other women achieve incredible success owning an at-home business in fitness. If you're ready for a new adventure and more choices, fill out my application. There is no perfect time. 

Disclaimer: BODi does not guarantee any level of success or income with the Coaching business. Each coaches income is dependent on his/her own effort, skill and diligence. Please see our statement of Independent Coach Earnings for the most recent info on actual incomes of our Coaches.

PS - Throwback photo from Turks and Caicos!

We couldn’t have dreamed up a better celebration for Colt, which ended with a glass bottom boat ride over a shipwreck. I am grateful to our family, friends & coworkers who showed up to support him. A fitting way to send him off on new adventures. 👨🏽‍🎓⚓️🎯

I’m in pretty good company on this Elite staircase. 😉IYKYK

Julie, Jenelle & I met as group fitness instructors 15+ years ago. We loved teaching classes as a hobby job in our “spare time” of working & raising kids. 

We all joined the Beachbody as coaches to help more people. It sounded fun, and it has been. We simply wanted more ways to share our passion for fitness.

Fast forward to today, we are still here, multiple time elite coaches in this amazing wellness company, now called BODi. 

PS- There’s more room on these stairs… for YOU! Let’s talk about how to get paid for your love of fitness! 

@jenellesummers @julievoris

I signed up for BODi 15 years ago to help people workout & eat better. As a working mom, I liked the idea of earning extra income on my time, doing something I loved. Simple. 

What I didn’t realize I was signing up for was a life-changing, community-filled dream-building adventure. 

Photo: this is moments before I opened the doors to my 11th annual Team Rockstar Fit day at Summit. We had more than 200 coaches from coast to coast attend our pre-Summit event & it was one of the best! Great energy, camaraderie, & learning. Jade was our official photographer. More to come.

So there you are, back in a vibrant city that you haven’t seen since childhood. The last time I was on the Riverwalk, my mom let me get my name painted by a local artist. I can still see it hanging in my bedroom for years. The letters were painted like flowers. 

I grew up traveling with my family — from TX to FL to MT. I loved adventure back then & I love it now, do you? 

Having the ability to travel to fun places for work is such a perk. This year I have been to Sundance for a board meeting, San Antonio for Summit, Scottsdale for a BODi leadership, event, and the mountains of Las Vegas for my own retreat. 

Do you love fitness & have a little voice whispering to be more adventurous? Yes or yes!

Have you ever practiced a presentation top to bottom in a bathroom with neon lights and a cement floor back stage? Twice? Me neither. 

But I’m glad I did before I stepped in front of 2,000 leaders. 🎤❤️

You can go solo in life. And do it all on your own. You can be bitter, jealous, skeptical, or look for excuses. And you’ll find them. 

Or you can roll like this. Cheering on other women, finding the joy, setting goals and smashing them. Someone has to. Why not you, too?

I teach women who love fitness to have an at-home business that opens more doors in life! 🤩

If that’s you, application in bio or DM for a quick call. Let’s see if we fit.

Have you ever sat down for lunch and walked out a better version of yourself?
That happened today. 

Damon West is an international keynote speaker and best selling author with a remarkably hard story. 

His first book was published just three years after his release from a Texas maximum-security prison for meth and robbery. He paid his dues and then some — the prison system is a violent place. 

But instead of becoming sad and weak, or mad and mean, he made himself a positive force in this world. Which is the premise of his book, called The Coffee Bean. (Read it).

Over a burger and fries, this guy is as humble, genuine and funny as they come. He’s curious about others and how he can use his life lessons to help them.

I met Damon through my friend Todd Durkin years ago and our paths crossed again when my son Colt used Damon’s quote in his senior yearbook. That reconnected us. 

So when Damon flew to northern Michigan to headline a huge speaking event, he invited us to lunch.

I couldn’t have asked for a better gift to my son, Colt, as he transitions from high school to a military prep academy later this summer. 

There are people in this world who are constantly trying to make it better. He uses his faith to serve others rather than to judge or control. He shares his grit, his belief & his dreams with others. 

PS- If you need that in your life, read his books, follow him on social media, or invite him speak to an organization or team that you are a part of. 

#beacoffeebean #coffeebean

On the last day of Pride month, the Supreme Court ￼delivered a blow to gay rights and all those who value anti-discrimination laws & equal protection. 

If the Supreme Court is politically & religiously motivated enough to declare that public businesses can deny service to people based on sexual orientation, they can also start denying services to people based on race, ethnicity and religious beliefs. 

Our parents & grandparents used to tell us about those days. But it wasn’t just gays, it was people of color, and Catholics and immigrants and anyone outside the majority. 

Heading down a very slippery slope and rolling back decades of progress. 

PS - for people who question the need for a Pride month, 
this is eye-opening. Would you ever be worried about a public business denying service to you based on who you are?

One year & a lot of life happened between these two photos. 🧡

Sunsets, laughter, travel, kids, sports, graduation, college, work, home addition, holidays, loss, grief, figuring out our roles, finding our groove, and most of all love.

Here is your friendly reminder that your health doesn’t take a vacation. 😅🇺🇸 

I started the holiday with a sweat in one of my favorite places with some of my favorite people! 

Before the lake, the drinks, the bbq, the bonfire, make time to move. A home workout, the gym or a walk!

Lessons I've learned the hard way. But they've served me well. 

You don't have to be happy all the time to succeed. You don't have to know all the answers. You don't have to be the most liked or most popular. In fact, don't be. 

You have to show up when it's hard. You have to figure out who you are and peel back the layers. Trust me. You have to let people go, you have to let self-doubt go. You have to trust your intuition and go figure shit out. Stop overthinking. 

If you want to collect the award or reward, shut out the gossip, the naysayers and your own inner critic. 

Get to work.

Have you ever made a decision that seemed so small and seemingly insignificant in the moment, but it led to an entirely different life? 

When I was a senior in college, a manager at a local health club asked if I want to become an instructor. This one small yes changed the trajectory of my life.  Years later, I was living in a small town in a new state. A group fitness instructor & friend asked if I want to join a company called BeachBody (now BODi) to help spread health and fitness to more people and earn extra money on my own time as a busy mom. I said yes, in a casual phone conversation while washing the dishes and watching my kids play out the window. 

That one decision changed the trajectory of my life. I looked back on 15 years in BODi, combining my passion for fitness with the ability to work for myself, and decide my own value and worth.

If you love fitness, and you have a bigger dream for your life, this is our time to talk. I love helping women make a seemingly small decision that leads to a greater life. 

I take my time and your time seriously. I invest in people who I work with. You can send me a DM or click on the link to fill out an application. I will grab a cup of coffee with you virtually and see if we are a good fit. Likely, if you are willing to bet on you, I am too.

When you meet someone doing what you aspire to do, are you excited or jealous of her? 

Me? So dang excited. Her success shows me what’s possible. I’ve always looked to female leaders for my own inspiration. 

I met a keynote speaker & author at our annual BODi convention. I loved her quick wit, pop culture references, and depth of ideas. 

I bought her book. I’m fully in it and leading 50 other women through it. It’s an easy beach read with little bombs dropped in.

I see my own book, I envision the chapters unfolding with stories & lessons. I see podcasting or presenting & I feel all the butterflies. 

For now, I’ll stay in my lane — growing & leading a top team of women in fitness, presenting for BODi when I can & running my local health clubs. 

I’m soaking up time with my kids & wife. Trying to not to live rushed for a bit.

But I see my future story & it excites me to know I have places to go & things to do in the years to come. 

Thank you @mrs.erin.king for showing up brave & reminding us all that we are a big deal. 😉

PS- shout out to my friend @heylgo my OG author/speaker bad ass friend. I’m so grateful to have bold, brilliant women in my corner of the world!

If you had to capture the last month of your life in 19 photos, would you like what you saw? 

Would you feel fulfilled? Would you feel joy? Would you feel at peace? Would you feel inspired? Would you feel strong? My answer is yes!

That doesn’t mean life is always picture perfect. It means that I’m right where I’m supposed to be. 

If that’s not how you feel in life right now, think about what changes you need to make. Is it your health or fitness, or who you’re surrounding yourself with, what you’re reading, or your goals (or lack of goals?) 

PS- I love mentoring women who love fitness who want to grow themselves and their dream. Every day you have a chance to build the life that you see in your head. Fill out the application in my bio. Or if that’s not for you, give yourself the gift of making the change that you do need.

I had an incredible summer evening with three great local friends — Sarah, Tracie & Amanda.

We sat on my friend’s patio and talked about business and life. We’ve been fitness instructors and BODi coaches for a long time. We have each helped a lot of people, changed a lot of lives, and built a business of our own as working moms.

I came home to this. I was stopped in my tracks. This is the life that I wanted to build. The one I saw in my head. These are the views that I want to see in every day life. This tells me that I’m just where I’m supposed to be. 

I love to help other women dream again. If you love fitness & are looking for an opportunity in life, let’s connect. 🧡

Part of being an adult is figuring out who you want to ride with in life. 

Also knowing who you want to be friendly with, but at an arms distance. 

Photo: Lion living his best life as my wingman tonight.

Want to take more days off? Choose a job that will pay you when you're not working. Even better, find one that you love, too.

As a long time fit pro, I did NOT want to burn out like so many do -- there is no glory in struggling financially or running ragged. I wanted a great life AND a career in fitness. 

That is why I teach women who love fitness to get paid from home, on their own time. 

I partner with BODi to help women have a business set up for them. You show up and do what you love -- motivate, inspire and create community. You don't have to write all the workouts, hunt for recipes or add another class or session to your calendar. Coaches are in demand. You have the skills. 

For the cost of lunch ($15.95/month), YOU can own fitness business -- no overhead, no rent, no additional certs or websites to build. 

I have a simple plan and I'll teach you. No social media, direct sales or experience required. Have an open mind. Income doesn't have to be that hard. 

I DO need your passion and your desire to help others move more, eat better and think better? You in? 

👉👉Send message for application. 

PS - This is from a recent trip to Mexico, paid for by BODi for helping people get healthy. It's that simple. Does YOUR fitness job or hobby do that for you?

Follow me for fitness inspiration, working out because you love it, and creating a life you don’t want a vacation from. It’s not built overnight, but over many nights. I help other women who love fitness bring goals to life with their own at-home business. DM or fill out application in bio. Let’s go.

I’ve loved the journey behind me with these two, and I’m excited for the journey in front of me. 

I disagree that you only have 18 years with your kids, only 18 summers, only 18 Christmas vacations. We have so many memories still to make. 

The seasons of life change, but we grow together, even though we are apart.

I was athlete growing up and now I’m an entrepreneur. There’s a lot in common. You have to be disciplined, work hard when no one is watching, and be open to feedback. 

But there’s one big difference. As an athlete, I needed a coach to pick me. I needed to be put in the game. That makes sense. Coaches are the ones who create the lineups, the ones who decide the playing time. But I didn’t always like the added politics— whose dad was volunteering, whose family did they know, and yes, of course who had the talent. 

But as an entrepreneur, I am 100% responsible for my own playing time and my own success. I pick me. When I fail, it’s on me. When I don’t show up, it’s on me. 

I love that mentality. I WILL show up for my own goals. Does that sound like you? If so, let’s talk. 

I’m hosting a one-day leadership retreat for my BODi team in November in Las Vegas and I’m looking for a few women who love fitness and want to EARN a seat at that table (we will also visit the pool in the spa!) 

I hope that hundreds of people scroll by this post and I hope that just a few read it and think “she’s talking to me…” That is who I’m looking for, and that is who I will mentor. Send the message. “That’s me.” 🙌🏻
Finding quotes like this remind me of the good of social media. This makes me feel understood. This is me.

In a funk? Frustrated by a situation at work, a friend or with family? Feeling anxious? 

I got myself out of a bad mood today by popping in my headphones in listening to @therealbrookecastillo 🎧 Her topic today was on helping people & the mental health benefits of doing so! Spoiler alert: it worked!
No I don’t think I can dance, but it made me smile when I needed it. Try it.

Portrait of my life at 47, with both of my kids in college. 

Finding joy in small moments. Finding peace in slower moments. Missing them & taking care of me.

Here’s the quick story. I discovered @brandicarlile about 20 years ago. I loved her voice, her lyrics & her vibe I guess. She was a new singer/songwriter from Seattle. 

Fast forward two decades, I’ve listened to all her albums on repeat, read her autobiography & seen her in concert four times. 

But this one was the best. She performed all acoustic, stripped down versions of her songs in an outdoor amphitheater on a lake in Northern Michigan. It was out of a movie. 

Another reminder in life to collect experiences, not things. Feels very relevant to me right now. 🖤🎵
I believe in a few universal truths. This is one of them. Fitness isn’t a choice or a chore. It’s a way of life.

I remember my daughter asking me on a trip once, when she was 13 years old, why a family member of mine never smiled. Even as a young girl, she was wise. She had discovered that happiness was an inside job. 

No amount of money, no body, no brand, no shopping cart, no business can make you happy if you are always keeping score, or simmering in a state of discontent. What if you want to escape that tiring state of life? I believe you can. 

You have to believe that your fingerprints matter in this world. Find ways to be of service to others. You have to love how you show up when no one is looking, when it's just you vs. you. You have to foster meaningful friendships. 

PS - I have stories, lessons and ideas on full pour right now. I've been writing and letting my mind wander about all the chapters yet to come in my life. Whether it's a stage or a podcast or a pen on paper all by myself at home. It's exciting to follow the path. I hope you come with me.

If ever given the choice to work up in your hotel room or get out & explore, you know what to do. 

I can easily get lost in my own head & my computer screen. But I’d rather get lost out here. Look at all these colors. What a gorgeous downtown. Way to represent, Grand Rapids. Michigan is the coolest state. 😎
Here’s the thing about success. You pick you. Bet on yourself.
Next time this happens to you, try this instead. I didn't know I needed this advice until I trudged my way through it. Flip it.

Around the holidays, an estranged family member told me to go “live my victim life on social media.” Then she hung up on me. 

That was unnecessary and untrue, but there’s a lesson in there. What that told me is that some people can only handle your highlight reel, your shiny parts, the pieces that are easy to love. Even if you fake it. But that’s not life.

We are all so much more. I share my ups & downs to help others feel seen or understood.  I like to write and speak. So I will. 

In the past week alone, I have woken myself up with worry, and I have also felt incredible joy in every day moments. It’s not one or the other. It’s all of it. That’s the way we experience life. 

BTW, I am a lot of things — bad at numbers, subpar at cooking, impatient, behind schedule. I need the pillows straight, and the counters clean. It’s a bit irrational. But I am never a victim. Because I won’t give my power away. 

And now you’ll remember that you don’t have to either. 🖤

“If you want to level up your life, level up your learning.” @brendonburchard 

It’s a daily practice. Stay tuned. More to come. 🤯

We are quite the duo. I’m terrible at baking and Erin’s daughter Avery is a first grader. 😳 But we decided to give my friend Holly’s protein cookie dough bars a try. We nailed it. Perfect for a treat in a school lunch, for after dinner, or maybe I’ll have mine with coffee in the morning. ☕️🍪

PS - I’m not a recipe guru. Don’t follow me for baking inspo. 😂I wanted to share this quick, easy one. If I can, you can!

Recipe reposted from @holly_hillyer 
1/2c almond flour 
1/3c vegan vanilla protein 
1/2c natural peanut butter
1/3c pure maple syrup 
1/2c chocolate chips

Mix together. Spread in baking dish. Refrigerate for 20 minutes & cut into pieces.
Raise good humans. The rest will take care of itself. Couldn’t love this young man more. 🖤

I remember when my kids were toddlers, and I started a side business online to help more people in fitness. I had no idea that that one simple decision to partner with BODi would lead to a lifetime of friendships, travel, adventure & more choices for my family. It has been work. And it has been worth it. 

I love mentoring other women who have goals, who are achievers, who aren’t afraid of to meet new people and join a fun community. Must love health & fitness & be willing to set some goals together! You know who you are. 

I invest time and people who I work with. If this is sounds like you, send me a message. We will coordinate a time to meet on zoom and have coffee.

Before I walked out on stage, to deliver the closing presentation at the BODi Leadership Retreat, fitness icon & legendary human @shaunt looked at me and said, “Trina, go out there and chase the feeling.” He told me the audience would remember how I made them feel more than they’d remember all of my words. ❤️😭

Stories, life lessons, fitness inspiration (as a way of life & an income) & stages of parenting. 

Those are the topics people value the most on my feed, so that’s what I’ll share.

Today’s lesson comes from me looking outside at our dock & hoist, I was reminded that it’s time to have it removed for winter. I thought to myself that I only knew one friend with a boat growing up, and I was invited on it one time. I loved it. 

But I never thought I’d ever have one of my own. As an adult, I became friends with another mom & entrepreneur, we’d get pedicures together & talk business and life! She & her husband had a boat & created so many family memories & experiences. I wanted that. So I worked for it. I bought a beautiful pontoon when I turned 40 & always credit the friend who showed me what was possible. We go to show others the way! 🖤

🎥 Photo throwback from my last trip on the pontoon this year!

I got fired from a great journalism job in Madison, as a stringer (freelancer) for the Milwaukee Journal Sentinel. I was 20-years-old and had been given a huge opportunity and side gig. But I blew it. I went out to the bar with friends and overslept my alarm the next morning. I missed out on covering a union strike at the Capitol. It was the teacher's union fighting for health insurance for spouses in a same sex marriage. No one covered the story for the paper and their voices were not heard. 

It was a wake up call to me. I stopped drinking liquor, have stuck to occasional wine or beer. I am glad that happened. I can't say I've ever been fired from a job or missed an important deadline since. And I have stuck to my own rules for consuming alcohol in moderation and never mixed drinks. It's just my thing. And it matters to me. Always honor yourself and have rules to live by that feel good to you! 

PS - this picture is from a recent trip to Madison, the place I fell in love with writing and first became a journalist!

The newly elected Speaker of the House said that same sex marriage would lead to other “deviants” being allowed to marry such as pedophiles & polygamists. He compared same sex marriage to being allowed to marry your pet. 

Supporting this religious extremist and the people who put him in one of this highest offices in the land, supports hatred and bigotry. You cannot wave a flag, celebrate freedom & deny human rights.

I don’t care what party you grew up with, or who you voted for in 2020, this is beyond leaning red or blue. This is bleeding straight hate. Don’t stand for it.

Erin and I got Rockford Peaches costumes for Halloween this year (yes, we need to iron them). But the irony is not lost on me. A League of her Own is based on a women's baseball team in 1943. In the Amazon series remake, they share the hard to watch stuff. Racism, homophobia, beatings. It was decades ago, yet here we are. 

I woke up again today with this heaviness. It's now 2023 (80 years later) and we an extremist in power in the House who is overtly hateful of gays, and compares us to pedophiles, calls us deviants. Says our marriage is like marrying a dog. I don't give one rip about the 2020 election or who you think should have won. I care about stopping overt hate. Let's get back to talking about education or environment or even taxes for God's sake. We have taken such a step back. 

This should not be accepted. But it is, and it gives others permission to be hateful and vengeful. I have experienced it in my own family. ===>>> What we make acceptable, becomes acceptable. 
Speak up, share. ❤️

PS - I'll go back to sharing fitness, motivation, success tips etc. But this just feels like a heavy lift right now.

This is my wife Erin. I’m proud of her journey. She lost 52 pounds after three kids and has kept it off for four years. She was sick of not being able to walk up the stairs with laundry. She was a former athlete who let herself go. 

She started working out at the gym and replaced her breakfast with a superfood shake. She loves using the high protein shake mix to make healthy treats on the weekends. 

This morning she made mini donuts. They were delicious with my coffee. Losing weight or keeping it off doesn’t have to be deprivation and doesn’t have to be strict. It just has to be consistent. 

Mini Cinnamon Donuts
Nonstick cooking spray
3 scoops Snickerdoodle Shakeology (DM me for a discount) 
½ cup oat flour
1 tsp. baking powder
1 pinch sea salt
3 large eggs, lightly beaten ½ cup plain Greek yogurt
2 Tbsp. pure maple syrup 1 tsp. pure vanilla extract 2 tsp. unsalted butter, melted
1 Tbsp. brown sugar
1 Tbsp. almond flour
1 tsp. ground cinnamon (optional)
Instructions:
	1.	���Preheat oven to 350° F. Lightly coat a donut pan with spray and set aside.
	2.	���Add Snickerdoodle protein, oat flour, baking powder, and salt to a small mixing bowl; stir to combine.
	3.	���In a separate bowl, add eggs, yogurt, maple syrup, and extract and whisk to combine.
	4.	���Add dry mixture to wet mixture; whisk to combine.
The batter will be thick! Scoop into a large plastic bag and cut a corner to pipe into the donut pan for less mess!
	1.	���Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into a donut comes out clean. Let cool in the pan.
	2.	���Then combine brown sugar, almond flour, and cinnamon in a small mixing bowl; mix well. Brush the tops of the donuts evenly with butter and sprinkle evenly with brown sugar mixture. Enjoy!

Four years ago, a sibling told me that my business would fall apart, my team would abandon me, and I’d would be a joke in my industry.

I’ve seen women fully transform their lives with the support of this fitness community. 

I’ve seen these women physically, emotionally, and financially becoming stronger. They take ownership. 

I’ve seen these women become gentle warriors of their own lives. 

I’ve seen these women break down, let go of past regret or trauma. Piece by piece, they become whole and grounded. 

I’ve seen these women lift up the next woman, place a hand on her back & see her. 

I am one of these women. And turning lights on for others is my calling, my purpose outside of motherhood.

You can weigh more than your "before." Photo on left: 18 months ago, 7 lbs lighter. Photo on right: today, and I felt amazing after my workout! I'm in my season of dealing with extra work deadlines, travel and unforeseen family issues (back home, not here). It's just real life. 

I haven't been sleeping as well and my nutrition hasn't been as on point. But I still workout daily at home and the club, (doing more Barre, Pilates and restorative Yoga), have a healthy shake for breakfast and lots of water. I show myself that simple habits work and I don't have to live perfect to live healthy. 

Overall, I'm striving for energy, no pain and more flexibility. I'm striving to live happy, free, and to serve at my greatest capacity. As an enneagram 3, it's always good to have a goal! 

I'm giving you permission. Your health goals can change in different seasons of life. At 48 years old, I'm in better shape than I was at 20 years old, so I'll take that! 

PS - If you need a plan or support for your current health goals, comment below PLAN. Let's connect. I can hook you up locally at BAC, or at home with BODi. Reach out by Friday 11/17 for a bonus gift of healthy snack bars!

What if you didn’t have to figure out life by yourself? What if you had a voice of encouragement or coaching to help you when you stumble, or to help you achieve. 

I started listening to and reading personal development 18 years ago when I was a young mom and business owner. It has guided me & it’s a huge reason that I have succeeded in business & grown as human being and mom. 

My current obsession is listening to a daily audio on a website that I subscribe to. It’s called Growth Day & it was created by high performance leader & author @brendonburchard 

I would love to share this with you. I will send you an exclusive link to the same subscription I have. I will personally check in with you. I have subscribers all over the country and the testimonials that are coming in are really profound — from a working dad who had a run-in with the law, to a CEO whose business closed, to a mom who felt like she was under a lot of pressure at work and home. They are loving it & feeling more alive every day. 

The “daily fire” lesson starts your whole day with calm & clarity. You are worth it. Send a message to get the link. Order by Nov 30th to get the bonus $10 Amazon card.

Want to stop hiding from 🙈 or worrying about 🫣 a situation and take action? 

Here are my suggestions:
✅ Worrying about the worry makes it so much worse. Rip off the Band-Aid and address the person or the situation. Face it.

✅ Find your calm & speak up. You don’t need to seek advice from 100 people. The more you talk about it, the bigger it becomes. Fix it. 

✅ Make the decision to confront, let go, or walk away. Trust that you can handle the outcome. 🙌

This works for situations, small and big. This week I addressed a false rumor that was spread in a medical office that caused unnecessary hurt for someone I care about. I have also used the suggestions to step back from friendships, or make tough management decisions at work or on my team. 

PS - this is actual video footage of my daughter’s cat Ruth Bader, who was hiding from the snowstorm! 

📍save this for later or share it to help a friend.

Life doesn't always deliver Hallmark endings, with the music playing and everyone hugging and laughing.

I watched the Happiest Season last night and loved (but hated) the ending. Not all family issues get tied up with a red bow. Not everyone comes around with love and acceptance. 

And so you keep going. And the sun comes up the next day. And you create your own life and accept that some endings offer new beginnings. 

PS - a photo from this time last year, with my sweet Layla, she was the best companion.

What can you rejoice in today? That’s what @brendonburchard asked in our personal growth lesson today. I’ve been thinking about it. 

❄️Christmas pj’s on a Friday night. 
❄️This sunset in my backyard. 
❄️A long talk with my ailing dad. 
❄️Coffee with a friend.
❄️A river walk with my wife & dog. 
❄️Hearing from both my kids. 
❄️Enjoying a book by the fire.
❄️Our holiday mantle.

When you seek health, fitness, real connections, positivity, dreams, plans & personal growth.

And you avoid drama, gossip, negativity, judgments, or staying small to appease others. 

Then life unfolds in a more colorful way. Those who see the world as you do will find you. Those who don’t? Won’t.

My mom passed away a year ago, on the Winter Solstice. She was 81-years-old, active and adventurous. Gone too soon. My mom had many hobbies— from quilting, to competing in agility trials with her goldens, to dancing in the Nutcracker, to taking group fitness classes. She was colorful. 

Our relationship was strained in her final years, my divorce and falling in love with my wife were understandably hard for her. But she didn’t want to talk about it. And I didn’t want to pretend. And so we were at a standstill. 

Everyone said she’d come around, but the pandemic, being isolated and far away, and sibling influences only created more of a divide.

A year after her passing, I’m looking at the decades of love and adventure that we had. From 2000 to 2019, when I was an adult with a family of my own, we took countless vacations with my parents all over the world.

From 2019 to 2022 when she passed, we shared occasional cards, emails, and photos.  We just needed to talk. We never did. As the divide widened, my siblings pushed harder against us.

I sent holiday gifts, and she sent plants for my birthdays and my wedding day (which tells we may have gotten there someday). 

As my dad nears his end of life, in his pursuit to join her, I’ll share more of the deep love and hard of family. Gratefully, my dad was able to move forward. She was not.

Writing is therapeutic. It’s okay to share real life. And when a family is run on image, it cracks. When we share, we help others feel understood, seen and whole. ❤️

According to my phone, I had 80 percent less screen time last week. What a gift. 🎁 

We escaped life, work, worries, stresses, hustle & bustle to explore Universal Studios as a party of eight. Trina, Jade, Colt, Eve & Erin, Evan, Owen, Avery ❤️

Endings are beautiful & hard. Doug Haag (1940-2023) was a great dad. A proud man. A son of an immigrant. A brilliant mind. 

He was never the life-of-the-party, rather a booth-in-the-corner guy. He loved a deal from Farm and Fleet. He was humble, never flashy. 

I was his youngest, and the only one with brown hair and eyes like him. That felt special.

He was a top criminal prosecutor. He had command of the law and the courtroom. His work was hard. Sometimes it made him hard.

He lived for his family. He never missed my games. He showed up in the bleachers in a suit and tie. He valued our vacations. He found peace in a trout stream and on a road trip listening to Buddy Holly. 

Even with kids of my own, I was still his daughter.  We continued to share about our lives. His in the law, mine in fitness. 

In recent years, when my divorce and marriage to my wife created division with my mom and siblings, my dad stayed quiet. He didn’t react. He reached on his own. 

He flew to Alpena when my daughter graduated, and embraced me, my kids, my wife, and her family. He was kind. We had dinner at my former husband’s house, he embraced him, too. 

He saw past black-and-white. He was able to see messy middles & beautiful endings. He didn’t offer his opinion or approval, he simply offered love.

In his final months, we had deeper conversations. He shared hard news with me. We both felt pain. 

He told me that my brother, and his law school classmate, helped my mom disinherit me. 
“They kept warning her,” he said. “They said that you chose a different family and were no longer part of ours. They said ‘that woman’ and her slew of kids shouldn’t benefit from anything of ours.”

It wasn’t his wish. But he stood by my mom, like always. He dropped his head and slumped his shoulders. This situation was outside the power of this powerful man. He gave me that gift of telling me on his own. We embraced. We cried. We moved on.

In one of my final visits, he told me that the photo album I made him after my mom passed was the most valuable thing in the house to him. 

I told him that I would share this story. I’m proud to be his daughter. I feel free.

I have some fun news to share about my fitness team (hint we hit a big goal!), but evenmore I have two tips to share on success that can speak to anyone no matter what your background or your job or your goals. Take a listen. ❤️

It took me a long time to figure out why I didn’t like competitive swimming in high school. I lacked the drive to beat others.

When I found team sports, like basketball, I found my groove. I liked winning with others. I loved the team, the vibe, the mixtapes for the bus rides, and yes, achieving a goal together. 

So it’s no surprise that as an adult I fell in love with leading a fitness team. For the past 12 years straight my team has earned the title of “Elite” team, meaning in the top 100 of the company, out of hundreds of thousands. I found my flow. I love achieving, and I love bringing others along with me.

To me, that is winning. Thank you Team Rockstar Fit for being an anchor in my life, for riding out the storms, and changing lives together. I built this team before ever knew how much I needed it. 

If you’ve been watching, this is your sign. I will help you get paid to be healthy and help others. If you enjoy achievement and working alongside other women, join our journey to an Elite team for the 13th year.

These pictures represent one of the biggest, boldest, cliff jumping moves that I’ve ever made in my life. 🥹With a toddler and an infant, I opened Bay Athletic Club for our community 18 years ago today, with an incredible team & lots of support from local family & friends. 

It’s been a roller coaster with heights and drops that I never could have predicted, but I would ride it all over again. We’ve impacted thousands of lives.

Take the risk. Do the thing. See the dream. Fail your way there. You’ll learn a lot about yourself along the way. And you’re wildly capable.

Happy 18th birthday, BAC. We have miles to go before we sleep. Let’s keep going!

It is possible to be wildly happy, relaxed and grateful, and also deeply sad, or angry. 

I have felt all of that on this trip. In my effort to share life beyond highlight reels on social media, I say that. I want to normalize feeling all of the complexities of life. 

I lost my dad on Christmas Eve. Every day a different memory comes to mind.  It’s like a fun gift to unwrap. I love remembering his advice, his words, his large looming presence in my life. 

As I think about the loss, I also have feelings of resentment. If you’ve been following my writing, you may know that before my mom passed away, she was pressured by my siblings, orchestred by my brother, to disinherit me, to shame me. 

My dad told me before he passed.  He was so sad. It’s not a story I wish to tell over and over. But it’s something that’s a part of me, knowing me is knowing that. And new lessons are born of it. I hope they help you in some way. 

On this trip, I’ve been listening to recorded conversations with my dad on my phone. They are healing. They are heart breaking & heart warming. He treated me with integrity. He treated me like his daughter. Because I am. 🤍

As I process the love & the pain, I am reminded that we are capable of handling hard feelings and still being excited for the sunrise tomorrow.
